<subSubSection pageId="601" pageNumber="602" type="diversity">
<paragraph pageId="601" pageNumber="602">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="601" pageNumber="602">Worldwide, with about 300 species in 32 genera (Lorenz 2005: 324-327). The Northern Hemisphere is represented by about 45 species (only 14.5% of the world fauna) and the Western Hemisphere by 55 species (about 18.5%). Seventeen species occur in North America.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
